Patterns & Best Practices

     * [http://ehealthafrica.github.io/couchdb-best-practices/]Best
       Practices - Best Practices, eHealth Africa.
     * [https://pouchdb.com/2014/04/14/pagination-strategies-with-pouchdb.
       html]Pagination strategies with PouchDB
     * [https://pouchdb.com/2014/06/17/12-pro-tips-for-better-code-with-po
       uchdb.html]12 pro tips for better code with PouchDB
     * [https://github.com/assafmo/couchdb-linux-performance]Linux tuning
       for better CouchDB performance

Map/Reduce

     * [https://pouchdb.com/2014/05/01/secondary-indexes-have-landed-in-po
       uchdb.html]PouchDB - Secondary Indexes
     * [https://cloudant.com/blog/mapreduce-from-the-basics-to-the-actuall
       y-useful/#.WIDBfRsrKUl]Cloudant - MapReduce Primer - Great intro on
       reduce, group, group_level.
     * [http://docs.couchdb.org/en/2.0.0/couchapp/views/joins.html#using-v
       iew-collation]Using View Collation - Index mapping (emits) for data
       joins.
     * [http://docs.couchdb.org/en/2.0.0/couchapp/views/collation.html]Vie
       ws Collation - More documentation on "View Collation".
     * [https://developer.ibm.com/clouddataservices/docs/cloudant/get-star
       ted/mapreduce-and-the-secondary-index/]Cloudant - MapReduce and the
       Secondary Index (Video) - Great videos here on mapReduce, secondary
       indexes, and complex keys.
     * [https://docs.cloudant.com/design_documents.html]Cloudant - Design
       Documents - Cloudant's documentation is also great resource for
       learning concepts of CouchDB.
     * [https://docs.cloudant.com/design_document_management.html]Cloudant
       - Design Document Management - How to manage design doc changes in
       production.

Joins

     * [http://docs.couchdb.org/en/2.0.0/couchapp/views/joins.html#joins-w
       ith-views]Joins with Views - Must read for understanding approach
       on doing efficient joins for CouchDB/PouchDB.
     * [https://docs.cloudant.com/transactions.html]Grouping related
       documents together in Cloudant - An approach that leverages CouchDB
       high availability nature.

Document Versioning

     * [https://wiki.apache.org/couchdb/Document_revisions?action=show&red
       irect=DocumentRevisions]Document Revisions (from wiki)
     * [http://web.archive.org/web/20100701165612/http://blog.couch.io/pos
       t/632718824/simple-document-versioning-with-couchdb]Simple Document
       Versioning

Blogs

     * [https://blog.couchdb.org/]Official Blog

Docs

     * [http://docs.couchdb.org/]Official Docs
     * [https://wiki.apache.org/couchdb/Frequently_asked_questions]FAQ
       (old wiki) - Seems to have more faqs than the
       [https://cwiki.apache.org/confluence/display/COUCHDB/Frequently+Ask
       ed+Questions]new wiki.

Books

     * [http://guide.couchdb.org/]The Definitive Guide - CouchDB's "Dog"
       Book.
     * [https://cwiki.apache.org/confluence/display/COUCHDB/Books]List of
       books on the Wiki

Videos

     * [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BKQ9kXKoHS810]10 Common
       Misconceptions - More videos from this
       [http://conf.couchdb.org/]conference.
     * [http://nosqltapes.com/]The NoSQL Tapes - CouchDB is discussed on
       [http://nosqltapes.com/video/hoffman-and-kocoloski-on-cloudant-and-
       couchdb]Volume 5 - CouchDB,
       [http://nosqltapes.com/video/understanding-mapreduce-with-mike-mill
       er]Volume 8 - MapReduce.
     * [http://www.oreilly.com/pub/e/1760]Scaling Out with BigCouch -
       O'Reilly video on scaling out with BigCouch.
     * [https://event.on24.com/eventRegistration/EventLobbyServlet?target=
       reg20.jsp&partnerref=cdc&eventid=1240121&sessionid=1&key=9E23B44802
       902EAD0BB2603F0434742E&regTag=35370&sourcepage=register]IBM - The
       New Builders Webinar Series

Libraries

     * [https://github.com/pandeiro/jaki]Jaki - A simple ClojureScript
       CouchDB client

Community

     * [http://webchat.freenode.net/?channels=couchdb]IRC -
       irc://irc.freenode.net/couchdb
     * [http://conf.couchdb.org/]Apache CouchDB Conf - Lots of video
       links.
     * [http://couchdb.apache.org/bylaws.html]Bylaws,
       [https://whimsy.apache.org/board/minutes/CouchDB.html]Minutes

Mailing List

     -dev is where developers of couchdb chat, -user is where users of
     couchdb chat and there's some crosstalk ofc -dev is appropriate if
     you're talking about changes to couchdb itself ("developer" doesn't
     mean you have to have a commit bit or anything) -rnewson

     * [https://mail-archives.apache.org/mod_mbox/#couchdb]Mailing Lists
     * [http://svn.apache.org/repos/asf/couchdb/site/htdocs/community/list
       s.html?p=900000]Mailing Lists Description
     * [http://grokbase.com/s/couchdb]Grokbase - Mailing lists in a
       [http://stackoverflow.com/questions/tagged/couchdb]Stack
       Overflow-like interface.

   [http://people.apache.org/committers-by-project.html#couchdb]The
   Amazing CouchDB Committers and Project Managers »

Companies

     * [https://www.couchbase.com/]Couchbase - NoSQL database.
     * [https://github.com/eHealthAfrica]eHealth Africa - Big user of
       CouchDB, check out their
       [https://github.com/eHealthAfrica/couchdb-best-practices]best
       practices.

Hosting

     * [https://cloudant.com/]Cloudant - Distributed database as a service
       (DBaaS).
     * [https://www.smileupps.com/]Smileupps - CouchDB hosting.
     * [http://www.iriscouch.com/]IrisCouch - Cloud CouchDB.
     * [https://bitnami.com/stack/couchdb/cloud/google]Bitnami Launchpad
       for Google Cloud Platform - Host CouchDB on Google Cloud Platform.

Related Projects

     * [https://pouchdb.com/]PouchDB - A pocket-sized database.
     * [http://hood.ie/]Hoodie - A backend for Offline First applications.

Misc/Technical

     * [https://web.archive.org/web/20160311144130/https://cloudant.com/bl
       og/dynamo-and-couchdb-clusters/#.WIEp4xsrKUk]Dynamo and CouchDB
       Clusters - Article about scaling CouchDB, using clusters.
     * [http://research.google.com/archive/sawzall.html]Google's paper on
       Sawzall - Exotic Reductions Examples.
     * [http://www.dimagi.com/blog/what-every-developer-should-know-about-
       couchdb/]What Every Developer Should Know About CouchDB - Article
       about lessons learned.
     * [http://www.nosql.se/2011/09/couchdb-maximum-database-size/]CouchDB
       Maximum Database Size
     * [http://horicky.blogspot.com/2009/11/nosql-patterns.html]NOSQL
       Patterns
     * [https://eclipsesource.com/blogs/2009/12/13/persistent-trees-in-git
       -clojure-and-couchdb-data-structure-convergence/]Persistent Trees
       in git, Clojure and CouchDB

Attachments

     * [https://pouchdb.com/2014/06/17/12-pro-tips-for-better-code-with-po
       uchdb.html]PouchDB - Attachments are overrated - "Update: since
       this post was written, the stability and performance of attachments
       in PouchDB has greatly improved. ..."
     * [https://docs.cloudant.com/attachments.html#performance-considerati
       ons]Cloudant - Attachments Performance Considerations
     * [http://grokbase.com/t/couchdb/user/14a1phbzrb/are-attachments-dupl
       icated-for-each-revision-as-well]Are attachments duplicated for
       each revision? - Mailing list discussion about attachments across
       revisions.

Backups

     * [https://developer.ibm.com/clouddataservices/2016/03/22/simple-couc
       hdb-and-cloudant-backup/]Simple CouchDB and Cloudant Backup -
       Article on IBM about backups.
     * [https://docs.cloudant.com/backup-guide.html]Cloudant Backup Guide
       - Cloudant docs on backups.

CouchApps

     * [https://couchapp.readthedocs.io/en/latest/user/list-of-couchapps.h
       tml]List of CouchApps
     * [http://ddoc.me/]Ddoc Lab - Create couchapps and CouchDB design
       docs right in your browser.

Scaling

     * [https://bitnami.com/stack/couchdb]Bitnami CouchDB - Bitnami makes
       it easy to run CouchDB in the cloud.

Resource Lists

     * [https://cwiki.apache.org/confluence/display/COUCHDB/Apache+CouchDB
       +Wiki]Official CouchDB Wiki
     * [https://wiki.apache.org/couchdb/]Official CouchDB Wiki (old) -
       Some things aren't on new wiki yet.
     * [https://docs.cloudant.com/guides.html]Cloudant Official Guides -
       Applicable to CouchDB.
     * [https://cwiki.apache.org/confluence/display/COUCHDB/CouchDB+client
       s]List of CouchDB Clients
     * [https://cwiki.apache.org/confluence/display/COUCHDB/Useful+utiliti
       es]List of CouchDB Useful Utilities
     * [https://wiki.apache.org/couchdb/Related_Projects]Old Wiki's
       Related Projects List

